{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Grease sides and line base of a square cake tin (23 cm) with baking paper.","Place chocolate in mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place orange peel and granulated sugar in mixing bowl then grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter, caster sugar, eggs and vanilla sugar then mix <b>40 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Add flour, baking powder and salt then mix <b>15 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add reserved chopped chocolate and mix <b>20 sec\/\/speed 3<b> then finish mixing in by hand with spatula. Transfer to prepared tin, then scatter blueberries evenly over the top, pushing some in gently with the back of a spoon. Bake for 40 minutes (180°C), covering with foil after 30 minutes to prevent top browning too much.","Leave in tin to cool then remove. Dust with icing sugar before cutting in squares and serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["200 g white chocolate, small pieces or callets (see tip)","½ orange, thin peelings of skin only","80 g granulated sugar","220 g unsalted butter, soft, plus extra for greasing","100 g caster sugar","3 medium eggs","1 tsp vanilla sugar, homemade","220 g plain flour","1 tsp baking powder","1 pinch fine sea salt","125 g fresh blueberries","icing sugar, for dusting"]}],"id":"r133668","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-GiIluhHDBTs\/XZWfNw0wDSI\/AAAAAAAAfAk\/Vfq5-gnsUcUqUQ_CippB_9TcWSsINlLNACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_qs06rgy0rcvqmfJh.png","title":"Blueberry and White Chocolate Traybake","publishedAt":"2017-06-12T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3 g","fat":"13 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"24 g","calories":"947 kJ \/ 226 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, aluminium foil, square cake tin (23 cm), oven","hintsAndTricks":["Cookidoo is full of inspiring cake recipes. Here, all of the preparation is done in your Thermomix, from chopping the chocolate to making orange-flavoured sugar and mixing the batter together. A great option when feeding a crowd, the pop of colour and flavour from the blueberries is simply delicious.","If using chocolate callets, omit <b>step 2<b> and add to mixture in <b>step 6.<b>"],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","20 pieces"]}